properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 18 at 3:12PM CST until February 19 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS TONIGHT ACROSS MUCH OF NORTHEAST
MINNESOTA...

.Dangerous wind chills are expected across much of northeast
Minnesota tonight. Wind chill values will range from 20 to
30 degrees below zero as an Arctic airmass settles over the
region. Frost bite is possible in as little as 30 minutes.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 35
below zero.

* WHERE...Southern Lake, Southern Cook, Northern Aitkin and
Carlton and South St. Louis Counties. This includes the Tribal
Lands of the Fond du Lac Band, the Grand Portage Reservation
and the Mille Lacs Band, Big Sandy Lake area.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 10 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 10 AM CST WEDNESDAY
